	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You can also get a few repro boards over at retrousb.com. Makes life a bit easier if its the right mapper.
<br />
<br />steps:
<br />Program you program onto rom. This process depends on your burner and software
<br />2.) Match the pinout of the (e)eprom with the mask rom in the cart and see what you'll need to rewire
<br />3.) bend up the pins that you need to rewire and solder in the rom
<br />4.) use wire to rewire the pins that had to be rewired
<br />5.) test it
<br />6.) ???
<br />7.) PROFIT!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
