	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />NROMs, CNROMs and SNROMs are name givien by Nintendo to their PCBs. There is plenty of these, and without telling us what mapper the game uses (so what PCB it should use) we can't help.
<br />
<br />As for rewiring, you need to compare the old pinout (the one that is on the board you use, such as SNROM) and the new pinout (the one of a 27Cxxx EPROM), and change the pins that doesn't match by cutting traces (or bending pins) and add wires. Yes of course they shoud not touch the PCB so that they don't make contact.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


